description:
Description
Weekly observations on prices and other factors from 1880–1886, for a total of 326 weeks.
title: CartelStability
reference: Online complements to Stock and Watson (2007).

parameters.season:
factor indicating season of year. To match the weekly data,
the calendar has been divided into 13 periods, each approximately 4 weeks long.
parameters.cartel: factor. Is a railroad cartel operative?
parameters.price: weekly index of price of shipping a ton of grain by rail.
parameters.quantity: total tonnage of grain shipped in the week.
parameters.ice: factor. Are the Great Lakes innavigable because of ice?

format: A data frame containing 328 observations on 5 variables.
